The paper proposes a novel approach to program synthesis, specifically focusing on synthesizing database queries. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.DB (Databases) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of soft constraints and user feedback to refine the sketch, which suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and programming languages (cs.PL). The iterative interaction with the user also suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HCI). Finally, the paper mentions scalability, which suggests a potential connection to software engineering (cs.SE).
